{"entity": "Control Unit", "type": "concept", "description": "Control Unit is a fundamental component of a computer that sends control signals to regulate the operations of other components such as the ALU.<SEP>Component of computer architecture that became more complex in second generation computers compared to the previous generation.<SEP>Control Unit (CU) là thành phần điều khiển của bộ vi xử lý, sử dụng thanh ghi điều khiển và trạng thái để điều khiển hoạt động của bộ vi xử lý.<SEP>A component that controls the fetching and execution of instructions, directed by the Next Instruction Reference to locate the subsequent instruction.<SEP>Control Unit (CU) controls the operation of the CPU and the entire computer.<SEP>Control Unit is a component of the CPU that directs the operation of the processor and coordinates instruction execution."}
